post_text:
HOMECOMING 2020
Grandview HS will be celebrating homecoming Friday, September 18, when the Zebras take on the Glen Rose Tigers. In accordance with guidance from the Texas Education Agency and the University Interscholastic League the events of the week will be different than in years past. For the first time the assembly introducing the Homecoming Court will be live streamed at https://www.zebrasportsnetwork.com/ on Thursday, September 17, at 9:00 a.m. There will be no parade or pep rally this year. Stadium capacity is still limited at 50% with tickets being sold to game participants first. Any additional tickets will be sold online at 8:00 on the day of the game. The crowning of the Homecoming Queen will also be live streamed on the Zebra Sports Network at zebrasportsnetwork.com We appreciate everyone’s understanding and look forward to seeing everyone at Homecoming 2020.

post_text:
New 2020-2021 School Calendar - www.gvisd.org/calendar

The board approved a revised calendar this morning for the 2020 -2021 school year. The calendar moves the start date back three weeks to August 26th for students and August 17th for staff. It will include face to face and online instruction.

In the spring the board approved a calendar that had three weeks built in throughout to use if needed. It started on August 5th for students with teachers starting on July 27th.

The new calendar is only a week later than we traditionally start and will allow everyone more time to prepare and make decisions for the upcoming school year.

UIL is scheduled to release information concerning extracurricular guidance sometime this week.

post_text:
La Transferencia Electrónica de Beneficios por Pandemia (P-EBT, por sus siglas en inglés) es un beneficio de alimentos único para las familias que perdieron el acceso a comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido debido al cierre de las escuelas. A fin de mayo, las escuelas les enviarán instrucciones para realizar una solicitud a las familias elegibles para la P-EBT. La solicitud de la P-EBT estará disponible la primera semana de junio.
Los beneficios de alimentos de la P-EBT son para los niños que recibieron beneficios de alimentos del Programa Asistencial de Nutrición Suplementaria (SNAP, por sus siglas en inglés) para marzo de 2020 y para los niños que estén certificados para recibir comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido en Texas durante el año escolar 2019-20. Para obtener más información, visite: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Good morning! We wanted to share the specifics for those who will be coming to pick up a packet at the Jr. High for their student on Monday. Pickup time will run from 9-11am.

Please enter the Jr. High parking lot on the HS side off of E. Tackett Ln. Pull up to the front of the school, and we will have folks there to bring your student's packet to you. You won't have to get out of the vehicle. (Please display the name of your student on a sheet of paper or card in your front windshield. This will help speed up the process.) Please know that at this time, only GVISD employees are allowed inside buildings.

We have only prepared packets for students who told their teachers that they did not have online access. If your child is using Google classroom with their teachers, you do not need to come pick up a packet.

If you have any questions, please call the Jr. High Office -- (817) 866-4660.

Today we activated student email accounts for Junior High and High School students. These student email accounts will be used to help with student/teacher communication. The students can access their new email accounts by going to www.gvisd.org/classlink and choose the gmail icon. They will login to the classlink page using their current student google account provided by the district. If your student has issues with logging in you can send an email to tech@gvisd.org for a password reset. The student email accounts are restricted to only emails within the district.
They can also use their classlink page to access other school resources that are available to them.

post_text:
IMPORTANT MESSAGE FROM GVISD:

Over the past few weeks, Grandview ISD has been actively monitoring the COVID-19 (coronavirus) situation and has remained in constant contact with health officials, the Texas Education Agency and local government officials who have been providing guidance and recommendations. Because the safety of our students, staff, and families is a top priority, we have decided to act out of an abundance of caution and will be postponing the return from spring break by at least one week. In addition, all campus events, field trips, student trips and UIL practices and competitions are postponed beginning Saturday, March 14, 2020 and throughout the closure. While we are hoping to be able to return to regular school activity on March 30th, we will be continually evaluating the situation and will keep you informed on whether the temporary closure will need to be to be extended.

Grandview ISD access codes are posted around the school campuses for students to access.

Six students walked away with the top awards during the ag mechanics show at the Johnson County Junior Livestock Show and Youth Fair this afternoon.

In the metal works senior division, grand champion was Colt Edrington of Grandview FFA (TX), with Juan Gonzalez of Cleburne FFA winning reserve champion.
In the wood works senior division, grand champion was Sydney Aalbers of Burleson Centennial FFA, with Madison Camp of Cleburne FFA winning reserve champion.

In junior ag mechanics, Mayce Ball of Friendship 4-H won grand champion, with Zane Ball of Friendship 4-H winning reserve champion.

post_text:
For those going to the Area playoff football game on Friday here is the Tyler Rose Stadium clear bag policy:

Fans are encouraged not to bring any types of bags inside CHRISTUS Trinity Mother Frances Rose Stadium during football games; however, the following outlines bags that are permitted:

Bags that are clear plastic, vinyl or PVC and do not exceed 12" x 6" x 12";
One-gallon clear plastic freezer bags (Ziploc bag or similar); and
Small clutch bags, with or without a handle or strap, that do not exceed 4.5" x 6.5" (approximately the size of a hand).
An exception will be made for medically necessary items after proper inspection at a gate designated for this purpose.

Prohibited bags include, but not limited to:

Purses larger than a clutch bag
Diaper bags*
Cases (camera, binocular, etc.)
Backpacks / Cinch Bags (includes clear backpacks / cinch bags)
Fanny packs
Reusable grocery totes
Mesh or straw bags
Duffle bags
Large totes

*Items normally carried in a diaper bag must be put into a clear plastic bag for venue entry.
text:
For those going to the Area playoff football game on Friday here is the Tyler Rose Stadium clear bag policy:

Fans are encouraged not to bring any types of bags inside CHRISTUS Trinity Mother Frances Rose Stadium during football games; however, the following outlines bags that are permitted:

Bags that are clear plastic, vinyl or PVC and do not exceed 12" x 6" x 12";
One-gallon clear plastic freezer bags (Ziploc bag or similar); and
Small clutch bags, with or without a handle or strap, that do not exceed 4.5" x 6.5" (approximately the size of a hand).
An exception will be made for medically necessary items after proper inspection at a gate designated for this purpose.

Prohibited bags include, but not limited to:

Purses larger than a clutch bag
Diaper bags*
Cases (camera, binocular, etc.)
Backpacks / Cinch Bags (includes clear backpacks / cinch bags)
Fanny packs
Reusable grocery totes
Mesh or straw bags
Duffle bags
Large totes

*Items normally carried in a diaper bag must be put into a clear plastic bag for venue entry.

post_text: Cadence is asking for help from her peers and school faculty for her community project with Grandview 4-H. Trex® has sent three recycle bins that have been set up at each campus. By collecting the most plastic by weight, will determine the winner. If our school wins 1st Place, they will receive a bench made by Trex® who also manufactures outdoor decking with recycled materials. Each school who participates will receive a participation award made by Trex® materials. Please have your children drop off any plastic grocery bags, bread bags (without the ties), sandwich bags from school lunches (have to be clean) the plastic film on cases of water, and dry clean plastic bags. Your contribution not only helps Cadence and our school, but helps our community and the rest of the world.

Softball Update
The Lady Zebras snuck out of Bryan with a 8-6 victory over Pollok Central. We will now be moving on to face a VERY good (35-2) #4 Buna in the regional finals. The winner will move on to the State Semi-Finals in Austin.

2 out of 3 series
Thursday. 6:00pm
Saturday 5:00pm
If game 30 min after

# 4 (35-2) Buna
Vs
# 1 (38-0) Grandview

We are visitor and 1st base dugout for game 1.
Home team and 3rd base dugout for game 2.
It’s a brand new turf facility.

Address

901 E Main St
Whitehouse, TX 75791

Hope to see everyone there!

post_text:
Yesterday the Grandview Colorguard solo and ensembles competed in Midlothian. Everyone that went got a superior rating! We also have three performances that made a score of 90+ which qualifies them for All-Stars this Saturday May 5th in Mansfield. We had one ensemble get a perfect 100 and the judge commented that it was the best of the 127 performances at the competition.

Solos:
Felicity Madore -1
Piper Tolleson - 1
Elle Baker - 1
Mady Lewis - 1 and advancing to All-Stars
Nathan Hinson - 1 and advancing to All-Stars

Ensembles:
Cassadee Merrifield and Gracie Roden - 1
Jada Argumaniz and Karla Gonzalez-1
Macy Caldwell and Nathan Hinson - 1
Kylee Grissam and Nathan Hinson - 1 and advancing to All-Stars.

post_text: Grandview High School and Julie Holloway were recognized for having a Distinguished Journalism Program today at Taylor Publishing. Mrs. Holloway teaches News Writing, Editorial Writing, Feature Writing and Headline Writing at GHS. Grandview and Mrs. Holloway have advanced students to the state meet for the past 15 years through their Journalism Program. Julie also received a 15 year service award from Balfour Publishing for 15 excellent published yearbooks. Congratulations to Grandview Yearbook, Julie Holloway and Grandview High School.
